@Image(source: ResourceReference, alt: String?) {
    ...
} Parameters sourceThe name of an image in your documentation catalog (’.docc’ directory). (required)

Omit the appearance (for example ~dark) and display scale (for example @2x) components. The file extension component (for example .png) is optional and can be omitted. For more information about the components of an image filename, see Adding Images to Your Content.

If the image name contains either whitespace characters, commas (,), or colons (:) you need to surround it with quotation marks (").
